                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/8799: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-11T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 11—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Semenoff who is now established at Grodekovo is endeavoring arrange for
                    transportation his troops through Manchuria to Trans-Baikal. If successful this
                    could only result in renewal lawless seizures merchandise and general
                    disorganization of communication with Trans-Baikal. Believe Chinese authorities
                    should be urged not permit Semenoff troops pass through Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
